<br>
Currently, we are at 8 guilds, and voted last eve to accept applications from guilds that qualify to join us. You have until February 1st to apply.<br>
<br>
How to Apply? Post on the Ideas section of the board listed below, having first please read our charter and gotten a feel for if your guild would be interested in joining.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub69.ezboard.com/bthefellowship62953">pub69.ezboard.com/bthefellowship62953</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
What would happen next ? We would ask that the guild applying be prepared to come to some of our events, get to know us. We would then need three sponsers from current members, and would then vote on the new guild joining under two months probation. During the probation period the applicant must run at least one event. <br>
<br>
Why might you join us?<br>
The Fellowship does not at all dictate the internal policies of each member guild, save that they keep to the alignment restrictions for their members. It is an association dedicated to making the world more fun for smaller family, and role play oriented guilds.  So that we can do larger things together, without having to ever say to anyone you have to raid x times a week, or leave your friends to join a large guild. Participation in any event is voluntary, and we respect those who do not do something for role play reasons.  We communicate via chat channel in game, and the message board outside.  Events may be roleplay / raid or combinations of the themes... (( for example lately we killed Cazic Thule as the evil LoS had stolen the soul of a paladin and this was the only way to get it back....)).  Each guild leader in the Fellowship has an equal voice in Fellowship decisions, we are a rabid democracy.<br>
<br>
